               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350302-name-1035" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350302-name-1035" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350302-name-1035" type="surname" value="HENDERSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350302-name-1035" type="given" value="WILLIAM OLIVER"></interp>WILLIAM OLIVER HENDERSON</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Powis-street, Woolwich. On the 26th of February, about ten o'clock, this pair of boots were brought to me by the policeman—I know they are mine, but I had not missed them.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350302-name-1036" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350302-name-1036" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350302-name-1036" type="surname" value="WARDEN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350302-name-1036" type="given" value="CHARLES STEWART"></interp>CHARLES STEWART WARDEN</persName>
                  </hi>. I am superintendent of police at Wool<lb></lb>wich. On the night of the 26th of February, I was in the street, and saw</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183503020172"></xptr>
               <p>the prisoner loitering about several shops—I watched him into Powis-street—he took from the inside of the prosecutor's door a pair of boots—the door was open—he ran away—he went into the door of a second-hand clothes shop, kept by Mrs. Miller—I went in and took him with the boots in his possession, under his jacket—Miller had examined them, and returned them to him.</p>
               <p>(<hi rend="italic">Property produced and sworn to.</hi>)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I picked them up, and took them to Miller to ask if she had lost them—she said, "No"—the officer came in and took me.</p>
               <p>
